                  </span></div><br><div class="comment">
                  <span class="c00"><i>I don&#x27;t think I&#x27;ve ever come across a guide for startups in such a situation.</i><p>Yep. I&#x27;m self funding a startup here in China. It&#x27;s hardware but not a kickstarter-widget, it&#x27;s necessarily relatively capital intensive to prove market-fit, the opportunity is large, it&#x27;s not in the US, it&#x27;s already multi-jurisdiction, it&#x27;s not growing via an accelerator, and it&#x27;s absolutely not an SaaS or similar. Getting any kind of current advice is really difficult! I feel your pain. Those of us who are outliers just have to learn to filter a lot of this stuff and keep what&#x27;s relevant. On the plus side, being outliers we probably have greater scope for execution without early competition, and if we play our cards right potential investors are more likely to notice us.<span>
