                  <span class="c00">Hey Patrick, I have one for ya. What are the biggest mistakes you&#x27;ve seen early, seemingly unimpressive founders (and teams) make during a pitch or through running their company that turned you off - only to discover later that they were able to build impressive businesses? Conversely, what signals do you think you&#x27;ve perhaps over indexed on (positively) in the past that have potentially been &quot;yellow&quot; flags in a founding team you&#x27;ve invested in (or recommended) and led to a failure to thrive? Are there things new startup founders can learn from either scenario?<span>
